{"body": "Just ran into this issue as well. I'd suggest a more robust approach however, since something like `MyModel.new(:integer_field => SomeOtherModel)` will still crash. So will anything that is not a `Hash` or `Array`.\r\n\r\n    assert_nil column.type_cast((1..2)) # test Range will fail\r\n\r\nProbably need to rescue out or check if the value responds to to_i.\r\n\r\nEDIT: Ah I see @jstirk already addressed this concern above.\r\n", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/11851923", "created_at": "2013-01-03T17:16:58Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/8718#issuecomment-11851923", "updated_at": "2013-01-03T17:43:35Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 8718, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jstin/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jstin/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jstin/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/jstin", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jstin/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/jstin", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jstin/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/5080ce38f03e6c7003742a8cb52eb1a1?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F32b9353318ce79aa3b2222b3fc3e79a6.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jstin/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jstin/received_events", "gravatar_id": "5080ce38f03e6c7003742a8cb52eb1a1", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jstin/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "jstin", "type": "User", "id": 247896, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jstin/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "5237f092bd3543c15100a2e3"}, "id": 11851923, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/8718"}
